cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with face verification using thermal and visible images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel Attribute Preserved Generative Adversarial Network (AP-GAN) for image synthesis, which falls under the category of generative models and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses deep networks for feature extraction, which could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves attribute extraction from images, which could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
